<emphasis id="3AB1EABBFF981B431A9CFD063565E7A0" box="[151,304,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Chrysobothris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: clypeal margin (Fig. 3), armature of the male protibia, apex of abdominal ventrite 5 (Fig. 5) and male genitalia. According to comments of my colleague Wolfgang Barries (
<emphasis id="3AB1EABBFF981B43198FFD6437EBE7CE" box="[900,958,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">in litt</emphasis>
., 
<date id="7C7B1069FF981B4319D9FD6430C6E7CE" box="[978,1171,706,729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="2009-02-25">25 February 2009</date>
), 
<taxonomicName id="CFC54D2AFF981B431EAEFD6430B7E7CE" box="[1189,1250,706,729]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fiji">
<emphasis id="3AB1EABBFF981B431EAEFD6430B7E7CE" box="[1189,1250,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">C. fiji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comes near to 
<taxonomicName id="CFC54D2AFF981B431F8FFD6435FDE7EB" authority="Kerremans, 1895" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costata">
<emphasis id="3AB1EABBFF981B431F8FFD6434B3E7EB" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">C. costata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6C544B58FF981B431AE6FD4335FDE7EB" author="Kerremans, C." box="[237,424,741,764]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="192 - 224" refId="ref1771" refString="Kerremans, C. 1895. Buprestides d'Indo-Malais. Annales de la Societe entomologique de Belgique, 39, 192 - 224." type="journal article" year="1895">Kerremans, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="90FE2A2CFF981B431BB3FD4335ACE7EB" box="[440,505,741,764]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,256,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,204,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-148@1.[151,1436,194,1726]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chrysobothris costata Kerremans, 1895. Figs. 2–6, Chrysobothris fiji, sp. nov., holotype: Fig. 2, dorsal habitus; Fig. 3, ventral habitus; Fig. 4, right foreleg; Fig. 5, frontal aspect; Fig. 6, apex of ventrite 5, ventral aspect. Scale bars = 1.0 mm; the same scale for Figs. 2, 3." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5305691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5305691/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<typeStatus id="D77E880BFF981B431803FD43360AE7EB" box="[520,607,741,764]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">syntype</typeStatus>
, BMNH) from the 
<collectingCountry id="70D27639FF981B431939FD4337B1E7EB" box="[818,996,741,764]" name="Northern Mariana Islands" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Mariana Islands</collectingCountry>
, differing by color, three pairs of elytral foveae and prominence of the elytral costae. 
<bibRefCitation id="6C544B58FF981B431875FCAE3741E608" author="Barries, W." box="[638,788,776,799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="77 - 81" refId="ref1450" refString="Barries, W. 2006. Zwei neue Arten deer Gattung Chrysobothris (s. str.) Eschscholtz, 1829 von den Philippinen (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Chrysobothrini). Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Osterreichischer Entomologen 58, 77 - 81." type="journal article" year="2006">Barries (2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6C544B58FF981B43192BFCAE370DE608" author="Barries, W." box="[800,856,776,799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="37 - 47" refId="ref1493" refString="Barries, W. 2008. Vier neue Arten der Gattung Chrysobothris (s. str.) Eschscholtz, 1829 aus Indonesien (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Chrysobothrini). Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Osterreichischer Entomologen 60 (1 - 2), 37 - 47." type="journal article" year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6C544B58FF981B431968FCAE37CFE608" author="Barries, W." box="[867,922,776,799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="51 - 54" refId="ref1540" refString="Barries, W. 2009. Chrysobothris (s. str.) jakli sp. n. aus Indonesien (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Chrysobothrini). Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Osterreichischer Entomologen 61 (1 - 2), 51 - 54." type="journal article" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
) has begun a long-term study of 
<taxonomicName id="CFC54D2AFF981B431F09FCAE31CEE608" authorityName="Eschscholtz" authorityYear="1829" box="[1282,1435,776,799]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3AB1EABBFF981B431F09FCAE31CEE608" box="[1282,1435,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Chrysobothris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the wider Indo-Oriental biogeographic region. He suspects that each Pacific island may have one, or more, endemic species, many of which belong to the 
<taxonomicName id="CFC54D2AFF981B431833FCEB3700E673" authority="Gory &amp; Laporte" authorityName="Gory &amp; Laporte" authorityYear="1837" box="[568,853,845,868]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="3AB1EABBFF981B431833FCEB36C8E673" box="[568,669,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">C. indica</emphasis>
Gory &amp; Laporte
</taxonomicName>
species-group characterized by having three pairs of elytral foveae and has seen undescribed species from 
<collectingCountry id="70D27639FF981B4318D9FCD63758E690" box="[722,781,880,903]" name="Palau" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Palau</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="70D27639FF981B43194AFCD637D8E690" box="[833,909,880,903]" name="Samoa" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Samoa</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
